{
  "texts": [
    "The literature also documented the use of mixed methods, including exploratory factor analysis and interviews.",
    "Furthermore, maturity models have been integrated into many studies as conceptual frameworks.",
    "Significantly, in the investigation of digital transformation challenges faced by SMEs, theoretical frameworks, including the \"Technology, Organization, and Environment\" (TOE) framework, absorptive capacity, dynamic capability theory, the information systems success model (IS Success Model), and the resource-based view were applied extensively.",
    "Table 1 offers a comprehensive panorama of research methodologies, theoretical frameworks, and thematic content about the digital transformation of small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs).",
    "This diversity implies a dynamic and multifaceted field with varied approaches to understanding this complex phenomenon."
  ]
}